Project state:
prototype / experimental
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Credits
	pete higgins (phiggins@gmail.com)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project description

This is the presentation base class. It provides a mechanism for various
display-oriented tasks. It includes a powerpoint-esque engine [prototype]
and an image SlideShow [experimental].

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies:

dojox.presentation requires both Dojo Core and Dijit systems.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation

See the Dojo API tool (http://dojotoolkit.org/api)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation instructions

Installation instructions

Grab the following from the Dojo SVN Repository:

svn co http://svn.dojotoolkit.org/var/src/dojo/dojox/trunk/presentation*

into your folder:
/dojox/

...which should be at the same level as your Dojo checkout.

and require in dependancies via dojo.require('dojox.presentation');

see /dojox/presentation/tests/test_presentation.html for example usage

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Additional Notes

The prototype engine works so far, but does not handle node-level 
actions ... (fade in a block, move a block, etc, etc) ... feel free
to offer up ideas in DojoToolkit.org forums.

